    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-08-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="640" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                <head>No. 78.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wurts</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-08-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 11, 1887</date>. (Received August
                                        27.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 136.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to aknowledge the
                                    receipt of your circular instruction of July 9, 1887, with its
                                    inclosures, relating to the proposal to remove tonnage and other
                                    charges on navigation, and to inform you that I have
                                    communicated the same to the Russian minister of foreign
                                    affairs.</p>
                <p>I remain, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George W.
                                    Wurts.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
